                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker—I have a pair of boots, pawned on 4<hi rend="italic">th</hi> Aug.; I do not know by who, in the name of Ann May. <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. LION</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi> These are part of the boots the prisoner got. <hi rend="smallCaps">GEORGE QUINNEAR</hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-sergeant, P</hi> 1). I took the prisoner on 11<hi rend="italic">th</hi> Nov. on another charge—I searched his house, and found ninety-five duplicates, and seven on his person—eight, found in his house, relate to those produced by these different pawnbrokers—fifty-six of them related to boots and shoes. <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> Most of them were my own manufacture, and some have been returned on my bands, and with money that I should have got next month I should have redeemed them. <hi rend="smallCaps">
